      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(openai): bound JSON/text response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nBound OpenAI provider HTTP response reads using shared provider helpers\nto prevent unbuffered JSON/text from untrusted upstream responses.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/openai/embedding-batch.ts` | `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared 16 MiB default) for batch status JSON. File content reader unchanged. |\n| `extensions/openai/openai-chatgpt-oauth-flow.runtime.ts` | `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB) in `postTokenForm` — must use raw reader to cap body before re-wrapping in `new Response()` |\n| `extensions/openai/realtime-provider-shared.ts` | `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared default) for client secret JSON |\n| `extensions/openai/image-generation-provider.ts` | Intentionally unchanged — already uses `readProviderJsonResponse` |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP proof: bounded reader cancels oversized stream\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_bounded_json.mts\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### Design\n\n- JSON paths use `readProviderJsonResponse` (shared provider contract, 16 MiB default)\n- Raw-body path (`postTokenForm`) uses `readResponseWithLimit` to cap before re-wrapping\n\n_AI-assisted._",
        "branch": "fix/openai-bounded-json-response",
